Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the complexity of hybrid logics over different types of frames. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as hybrid logics are used in knowledge representation and reasoning, which is a subfield of AI. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possibility as the paper discusses the complexity of satisfiability problems. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possibility as the paper analyzes the computational complexity of hybrid logics over different types of frames. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with the semantics and syntax of hybrid logics.
